ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: It's probably been said somewhere on this site before, but it's true: the Chinese language program at Yale is an incredibly well-oiled machine. Students should "know what they're getting into," true, but they can also expect a clear sense of organization and consistent, fair grading. Professors Wang and Chan are both incredible - brilliant and energetic. I was grateful to be learning from them every time I walked into class.
